SIMPLE: exacerbation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Exacerbation
<hw>Ex*ac`er*ba"tion</hw>
<pr>(⟦ecr⟧gz*⟦acr⟧s`⟦etil⟧r*b⟦amac⟧"sh⟦ucr⟧n)</pr> <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. F. <ets>exacerbation</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of
rendering more violent or bitter; the state of being exacerbated or
intensified in violence or malignity; <as>as, <ex>exacerbation</ex> of
passion</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A periodical increase of violence
in a disease, as in remittent or continuous fever; an increased energy
of diseased and painful action.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Exacerbescence</ent>⟦br⟧
